# React And TypeScript

- Prefer TypeScript and avoid `any` unless the surrounding code already requires it.
- Use functional React components and hooks; avoid class components.
- Read nearby components, hooks, and utilities before adding new patterns.
- Keep imports organized: external dependencies, internal modules, then styles.
- Extract reusable logic into focused hooks or utilities when it reduces meaningful duplication.
- Add TSDoc/JSDoc for complex public APIs, exported helpers, or non-obvious contracts.
- Keep changes compatible with the project’s package manager, framework version, and existing test stack.
